description.plain:
Professionally as Anne-Marie, Anne-Marie Nicholson is a British pop singer. She began her singing career when she produced a demo for Rocket Records in 2013 titled “Summer Girl.” Her solo career was curtailed in order for her to develop herself as an artist.

Nicholson caught the attention of Rudimental when one of their vocalists left; they asked Anne-Marie to replace her. She featured on four tracks on their album We the Generation, and spent two years touring alongside them.
Her debut EP, Karate, was released via Atlantic and Major Tom’s in late 2015. In early 2016, she released “Do It Right”, which was followed by her breakthrough single “Alarm”. The Clean Bandit and Sean Paul collaboration “Rockabye” was an even bigger success, becoming the UK Christmas #1 in 2016.

Three singles were released from her debut album in 2017: “Ciao Adios”, “Heavy” and “Then”. The hit collaboration with Marshmello, “FRIENDS” preceded her long-awaited debut, Speak Your Mind, released in April 2018.

description.plain:
In “2002,” Anne-Marie reminisces about falling in love as an 11-year-old and all the songs that soundtracked that romance. She had some help from Ed Sheeran to write this track.

During the song’s chorus, she references six songs released in the late 1990s and early 2000s, like Jay-Z’s “99 Problems,” Nelly’s “Ride wit Me,” NSYNC’s “Bye Bye Bye” and Britney Spears' “…Baby One More Time.”

The “99 Problems” reference is actually a misnomer, however, as Jay-Z didn’t write that song until 2003.

songs.title: Alarm

description.plain:
UK upstart Anne-Marie dropped this single in May 2016, along with press release that read:

‘Alarm’ is about somebody I was dating and I guess I just always had a suspicion that he was doing something naughty. I’m a bit of an investigator and I found out my inkling was right! The thing is, he left someone to be with me and I always thought he could do it again. I love this song so much and I hope you love it too!

Production was handled by Steve Mac with assistance from Amir Amor, who is part of the UK drum and bass band Rudimental. Anne-Marie was the vocalist that toured with Rudimental for two years, and also signed to their label, Major Tom. Steve Mac (and writing partners Wayne Hector and Ina Wroldsen) are the pop confection-half of this song. They’ve worked with major acts like Britney Spears, One Direction, and Nicki Minaj.

songs.title: Ciao Adiós

description.plain:
Premiered during her late 2016 UK Tour, ‘Ciao Adios’ is one of the songs Anne-Marie has written and recorded for her debut album.

The track is about how she found out the subject (her now, ex-boyfriend) was having an affair, and how he is now doing all the things he used to do with her, with his new girlfriend.

“Ciao Adios” translates to English to “Bye, bye”, meaning that Anne-Marie is now done with her ex-boyfriend, and realises she doesn’t need him anymore, and is saying bye to get a form of closure.

The official video of ‘Ciao Adios’ was released March 9, 2017.
